  "description": "Context\n-------\nGlobal entry point for Loki logs generated by Docker workloads in the homelab.  \nIt exposes the same stack → service → container model used in the Docker\ncontainers overview dashboard, but focused on error-level log activity and\nguided troubleshooting.\n\nFocus\n-----\nHelp answer, in a few seconds:\n- Which stack is currently generating the most error-level logs?\n- Within that stack, which services are the noisiest?\n- How have error rates evolved over time for a given service?\n- What do the actual error log lines look like, and what else is the\n  service logging around those errors?\n\nImplementation\n--------------\n- Data source: Loki, restricted to `job=\"dockerlogs\"` as ingested by Promtail.\n- Label model:\n  - `stack` → logical stack (nextcloud, monitoring, cloudflared, etc.).\n  - `compose_service` → Docker Compose service name (grafana, loki, nc-web, etc.).\n  - `container` → concrete container instance.\n- Error views (rows 1 and 2) use a consistent filter:\n  `|~ \"level=(error|critical|fatal|panic)\"` to focus on error/critical/fatal\n  log entries.\n- Raw view (row 3) shows all log levels for the selected stack/service/container\n  and adds a free-text `$search` box for ad-hoc investigations.\n\nRow layout:\n- Row 1 – Stack and service error overview:\n  - Error log volume by stack (time series).\n  - Top services by error volume within the selected stack(s).\n- Row 2 – Selected service error detail:\n  - Error log volume over time (5m buckets) for the chosen service.\n  - Recent error log samples for that service (and container, if specified).\n- Row 3 – Raw logs with search:\n  - Full-text Loki view for the same filters, with optional `$search`\n    substring matching.\n\nSecurity / operational impact\n-----------------------------\n- The dashboard does not introduce new log fields or data sources; it\n  only organises existing Loki logs based on standard labels and level\n  patterns.\n- All retention, RBAC and access controls are inherited from the Loki\n  datasource configuration.\n- Aggregated panels (volumes, rankings) only show counts per stack/service,\n  while detailed contents are confined to dedicated log panels that are\n  equivalent to using Explore with the same filters.",
